+.. SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
+
+========================================
+io_uring Low-Latency Completion Mode
+========================================
+
+The ``IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY`` flag is an experimental feature designed to
+reduce latency variance in deterministic workloads.
+
+Overview
+--------
+
+Low-latency mode prioritizes execution speed and determinism over CPU power
+consumption.
+
+Behavioral Changes
+------------------
+
+When ``IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY`` is enabled:
+
+1. **Busy-Wait Polling**: The ``io_uring_enter`` system call will perform a
+   short busy-wait loop (polling) before falling back to a sleeping wait.
+
+2. **Immediate Notification**: The kernel forces the use of immediate
+   notification (``TWA_SIGNAL``) for task work.
+
+Tradeoffs
+---------
+
+- **CPU Usage**: significantly higher.
+- **Latency**: significantly lower and more deterministic.
+
+Usage
+-----
+
+To enable this mode, set the ``IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY`` bit in the
+``flags`` field of ``struct io_uring_params``.
+
+::
+
+    params.flags |= IORING_SETUP_LOW_LATENCY;
+
